2020 |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|style=\"background:#BBCDE4\" |'''38'''\t<!-- Likud\t\t-->\n|16\t\t\t\t\t<!-- B&W\t\t-->\n|14\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yesh Atid-Telem\t-->\n|15\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Joint List\t\t-->\n|9\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Shas\t\t-->\n|8\t\t\t\t\t<!-- UTJ\t\t-->\n|8\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yisrael Beiteinu\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yamina\t\t-->\n|5\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Meretz\t\t-->\n|{{small|(2.85%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Derekh Eretz\t-->\n|{{small|(0.93%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Gesher\t\t-->\n|{{small|(0.60%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Otzma\t\t-->\n|-\n|}\n\n== Prime minister ==\nDue to the [[political deadlock]], [[Shas]] chairman and [[Interior Minister of Israel|Interior Minister]] [[Aryeh Deri]] suggested [[direct election]]s for [[Prime Minister of Israel|prime minister]].<ref name=direct>{{cite news |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/poll-predicts-slight-edge-for-netanyahu-over-gantz-if-direct-elections-were-held/ |title=Poll predicts slight edge for Netanyahu over Gantz if direct elections were held |work=[[The Times of Israel]] |date=5 November 2019 |accessdate=7 November 2019}}</ref> Some opinion pollsters have asked voters which party leader they would prefer as prime minister. Their responses are given as percentages in the tables below.\n\n;Netanyahu vs Gantz\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; line-height:13px;\"\n!rowspan=2 |Date\n!rowspan=2 |Polling firm\n!rowspan=2 |Publisher\n![[Benjamin Netanyahu|Netanyahu]]\n![[Benny Gantz|Gantz]]\n!Neither\n!Don't Know\n|-\n!style=\"background:{{Likud/meta/color}}\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Blue and White/meta/color}}\" |\n!style=\"background:#d3d3d3\" |\n!style=\"background:#ffffff\" |\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-03-13\" |13 Mar 2020\n|Maagar Mohot\n|''[[Israel Hayom]]''<ref name=IH13Mar>{{cite news |title=\u05e1\u05e7\u05e8 \"\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc \u05d4\u05d9\u05d5\u05dd\": \u05d4\u05e8\u05d5\u05d1 \u05e0\u05d2\u05d3 \u05de\u05de\u05e9\u05dc\u05ea \u05de\u05d9\u05e2\u05d5\u05d8 |url=https://www.israelhayom.co.il/article/741567 |lang=he |author=Amnon Lord |work=[[Israel Hayom]] |date=13 March 2020 |accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n|style=\"background:#BBCDE4\" |'''47'''\t<!-- Netanyahu\t-->\n|36\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Gantz\t-->\n|\u2013\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Neither\t-->\n|17\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Don't Know\t-->\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-03-12\" |12 Mar 2020\n|Midgam\n|[[Channel 12 (Israel)|Channel 12]]<ref name=Ch12Mar12/>\n|style=\"background:#BBCDE4\" |'''45'''\t<!-- Netanyahu\t-->\n|33\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Gantz\t-->\n|14\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Neither\t-->\n|8\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Don't Know\t-->\n|}\n\n== Coalition ==\nSome opinion pollsters have asked voters which coalition they would prefer. The tables below list their responses as percentages.\n\n;[[Minority government]] backed by the [[Joint List]]\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; line-height:13px\"\n!Date\n!Polling firm\n!Publisher\n!Support\n!Oppose\n!Don't Know\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-03-13\" |13 Mar 2020\n|Maagar Mohot\n|''[[Israel Hayom]]''<ref name=IH13Mar/>\n|31\n|style=\"background:pink\" |'''55'''\n|14\n|}\n\n;General\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; line-height:13px\"\n!rowspan=2 |Date\n!rowspan=2 |Polling firm\n!rowspan=2 |Publisher\n!colspan=2 |[[National unity government]]\n!rowspan=2 |[[Right-wing politics|Right]]\n!rowspan=2 |[[Left-wing politics|Left]]\n!rowspan=2 |Don't Know\n|-\n![[Likud]]-[[Blue and White (political alliance)|B&W]] only\n!w/ more parties\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-03-13\" |13 Mar 2020\n|Maagar Mohot\n|''[[Israel Hayom]]''<ref name=IH13Mar/>\n|17\n|style=\"background:Violet\" |'''31'''\n|26\n|17\n|9\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Opinion polling in Israel|next legislative election]]\n[[Category:Opinion polling for future elections|Israeli legislative]]\n", "text_old": "In the run up to the [[next Israeli legislative election]], various organisations carry out [[opinion poll]]ing to gauge voting intention in [[Israel]] during the term of the [[23rd Knesset]]. This article lists the results of such polls.\n\nThe date range for these opinion polls is from the [[2020 Israeli legislative election|previous election]], held on 2 March 2020, to the present day. The next election is scheduled to be held on 5 November 2024. However, due to the [[political deadlock]] which resulted after the previous election, a fourth consecutive [[snap election]] is possible.<ref name=Gesher/> Therefore polling for the next election started as soon as 10 days after the previous election.<ref name=Ch12Mar12/> [[election silence|No polls may be published]] from the end of the Friday before the election until the [[polling station]]s close on election day at 22:00.<ref name=silence>[[s:he:\u05d7\u05d5\u05e7 \u05d4\u05d1\u05d7\u05d9\u05e8\u05d5\u05ea (\u05d3\u05e8\u05db\u05d9 \u05ea\u05e2\u05de\u05d5\u05dc\u05d4)#\u05e1\u05e2\u05d9\u05e3 16\u05d4]] (\u05d7) (in Hebrew)</ref>\n\nPolls are listed in reverse chronological order, showing the most recent first and using the dates when the survey fieldwork was done, as opposed to the date of publication. Where the fieldwork dates are unknown, the date of publication is given instead. The highest figure in each polling survey is displayed with its background shaded in the leading party's colour. If a tie ensues, this is applied to the highest figures. When a poll has no information on a certain party, that party is instead marked by a dash (\u2013).\n\n== Seat projections ==\nThis section displays voting intention estimates referring to a hypothetical [[Knesset]] election. The figures listed are Knesset seat counts rather than percentages, unless otherwise stated.\n\n=== Graphs ===\nThis graph shows the polling trends from the 2 March [[2020 Israeli legislative election]] until the next election day using 4-poll [[moving average]]. Scenario polls are not included here.\n\nFor parties not crossing the [[electoral threshold]] (currently 3.25%) in any given poll, the number of seats is calculated as a percentage of the 120 total seats.\n\n{{Graph:Chart |width=650 |height=600 |xAxisTitle=Date |yAxisTitle=Seats |legend= |type=line\n|interpolate=basis\n|xType=date\n|xAxisMax = 1733178400000\n|yAxisMin=0\n|yGrid=5\n|x= 2020/03/02, 2020/03/12, 2020/03/16,\t2020/03/19, 2020/03/27, 2020/03/30, 2020/04/01, 2020/04/07, 2020/04/13\n|y1Title=Likud\t\t\t|y1=\t36,\t37,\t38,\t38.667,\t38.5,\t39.25,\t39.75,\t42,\t40\n|y2Title=Blue and White\t\t|y2=\t17,\t,\t,\t,\t15,\t15,\t16.67,\t18,\t19\n|y3Title=Yesh Atid-Telem\t|y3=\t16,\t,\t,\t,\t16,\t13.5,\t12,\t9,\t10\n|y4Title=Joint List\t\t|y4=\t15,\t15,\t15.5,\t15.333,\t15.25,\t15.5,\t15.5,\t16,\t15\n|y5Title=Shas\t\t\t|y5=\t9,\t9,\t8.5,\t8.333,\t8.25,\t8.25,\t8.5,\t8,\t9\n|y6Title=UTJ\t\t\t|y6=\t7,\t7,\t7.5,\t7.333,\t7.25,\t7.25,\t7,\t7,\t8\n|y7Title=Yisrael Beiteinu\t|y7=\t7,\t7,\t6.5,\t6.667,\t6.5,\t6.25,\t6.25,\t6,\t7\n|y8Title=Labor-Meretz\t\t|y8=\t6,\t,\t7,\t6.5,\t7,\t7.5,\t7.25,\t7,\t5\n|y9Title=Yamina\t\t\t|y9=\t6,\t6,\t6,\t6.333,\t6.5,\t6.75,\t6.75,\t7,\t8\n|y10Title=Gesher\t\t|y10=\t1,\t,\t2.1,\t1.296,\t1.384,\t\n|y11Title=Otzma Yehudit\t\t|y11=\t0.504,\t0.84,\t0.624,\t0.536,\t0.597,\t\n|y12Title=Threshold (3.25%)\t|y12=\t3.9,\t3.9,\t3.9,\t3.9,\t3.9,\t3.9,\t3.9,\t3.9,\t3.9\n|colors=#1f5aa5,#00D5FF,#003BA3,#01B2AC,#000000,#385380,#9AC0E2,#EE1C25,#B7CC15,#ED0963,#2441FF,#808080\n}}\n\n=== Polls ===\nPoll results are listed in the table below. Parties that fall below the [[electoral threshold]] are denoted by the percentage of votes that they received (N%) rather than the number of seats they would have gotten.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:90%;line-height:13px\"\n!rowspan=2 |Date\n!rowspan=2 |Polling firm\n!rowspan=2 |Publisher\n![[Likud]]\n![[Yesh Atid-Telem|Yesh Atid-<br/>Telem]]\n![[Blue and White (political alliance)|Blue &<br>White]]\n![[Joint List|Joint<br/>List]]\n![[Shas]]\n![[United Torah Judaism|UTJ]]\n![[Yisrael Beiteinu|Yisrael<br/>Beiteinu]]\n![[Yamina (political alliance)|Yamina]]\n![[Israeli Labor Party|Labor]]\n![[Meretz]]\n![[Derekh Eretz (political party)|Derekh<br/>Eretz]]\n![[Gesher (2019 political party)|Gesher]]\n![[Otzma Yehudit|Otzma]]\n|-\n!style=\"background:{{Likud/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:#003BA3;\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Blue and White (political alliance)/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Joint List/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Shas/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:{{United Torah Judaism/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Yisrael Beiteinu/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Yamina/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Israeli Labor Party/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Meretz/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:#203367;\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Gesher (2019 political party)/meta/color}};\" |\n!style=\"background:{{Otzma Yehudit/meta/color}};\" |\n|- style=\"background:silver\"\n|colspan=3 |'''Current seats'''\n|style=\"background:#BBCDE4\" |'''36'''\t<!-- Likud\t\t-->\n|16\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yesh Atid-Telem\t-->\n|15\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Resilience\t\t-->\n|15\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Joint List\t\t-->\n|9\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Shas\t\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- UTJ\t\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yisrael Beiteinu\t-->\n|6\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yamina\t\t-->\n|3\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Labor\t\t-->\n|3\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Meretz\t\t-->\n|2\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Derekh Eretz\t-->\n|1\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Gesher\t\t-->\n|\u2013\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Otzma\t\t-->\n|-\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-04-07\" |13 Apr 2020\n|Smith\n|''[[Channel 12 (Israel)|N12]]''<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mako.co.il/news-politics/2020_q2/Article-110e0ba84547171027.htm\n|title=Poll N12: Right-wing ultra-Orthodox bloc strengthens to 64 seats, center-left suffers 34 |work=Jeremy's Knesset Insider |date=13 April 2020 |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n|style=\"background:#BBCDE4\" |'''40'''\t<!-- Likud\t\t-->\n|10\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yesh Atid-Telem\t-->\n|19\t\t\t\t\t<!-- B&W\t\t-->\n|15\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Joint List\t\t-->\n|9\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Shas\t\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- UTJ\t\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yisrael Beiteinu\t-->\n|8\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yamina\t\t-->\n|{{small|(1.1%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Labor\t\t-->\n|5\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Meretz\t\t-->\n|{{small|(1.4%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Derekh Eretz\t-->\n|{{small|(1.4%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Gesher\t\t-->\n|{{small|(1.9%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Otzma\t\t-->\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-04-07\" |7 Apr 2020\n|Smith\n|''[[The Jerusalem Post]]''<ref>{{cite news |url=https://knessetjeremy.com/2020/04/08/7th-poll-of-possible-4th-elections-likud-42-blue-white-18-joint-list-16-yesh-atid-9-approval-ratings-68-netanyahu-65-bennett-28-litzman/ |title=7th Poll of Possible 4th Elections: Likud 42, Blue & White 18, Joint List 16, Yesh Atid 9; Approval Ratings: 68% Netanyahu, 65% Bennett, 28% Litzman |work=Jeremy's Knesset Insider |date=8 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|style=\"background:#BBCDE4\" |'''42'''\t<!-- Likud\t\t-->\n|9\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yesh Atid-Telem\t-->\n|18\t\t\t\t\t<!-- B&W        \t-->\n|16\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Joint List\t\t-->\n|8\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Shas\t\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- UTJ\t\t-->\n|6\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yisrael Beiteinu\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yamina\t\t-->\n|{{small|(2.2%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Labor\t\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Meretz\t\t-->\n|{{small|(0.3%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Derekh Eretz\t-->\n|{{small|(0.9%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Gesher\t\t-->\n|{{small|(0.9%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Otzma\t\t-->\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-04-06\" |6 Apr 2020\n|colspan=15 |'''[[Israeli Labor Party|Labor]] splits from [[Meretz]]'''<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Labor-to-merge-with-Benny-Gantzs-Blue-and-White-party-623766 |title=Labor to merge with Benny Gantz's Blue and White party |author=Gil Hoffman |work=[[The Jerusalem Post]] |date=6 April 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:90%;line-height:13px\"\n!rowspan=2 |Date\n!rowspan=2 |Polling firm\n!rowspan=2 |Publisher\n![[Likud]]\n![[Blue and White (political alliance)|B