5 MKs |work=Jeremy's Knesset Insider |date=27 March 2020 |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n|style=\"background:#BBCDE4\" |'''38'''\t<!-- Likud\t\t-->\n|15\t\t\t\t\t<!-- B&W\t\t-->\n|16\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yesh Atid-Telem\t-->\n|15\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Joint List\t\t-->\n|8\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Shas\t\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- UTJ\t\t-->\n|6\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yisrael Beiteinu\t-->\n|8\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Labor\u2013Meretz\t-->\n|7\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Yamina\t\t-->\n|{{small|(1.3%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Gesher\t\t-->\n|{{small|(0.65%)}}\t\t\t<!-- Otzma\t\t-->\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-03-26\" |26 Mar 2020\n|colspan=13 |'''[[Yesh Atid]] and [[Telem (2019 political party)|Telem]] unofficially split from [[Blue and White (political alliance)|Blue and White]]'''<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Politics-And-Diplomacy/Likud-Blue-and-White-negotiations-intensifying-622426 |title=Blue and White splitting after Benny Gantz elected Knesset Speaker |author=Gil Hoffman |work=[[The Jerusalem Post]] |date=26 March 2020 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-03-23\" |23 Mar 2020\n|colspan=13 |'''[[Gesher (2019 political party)|Gesher]] splits from [[Israeli Labor Party|Labor]] and [[Meretz]]'''<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog_entry/you-can-go-your-own-way-arrangements-committee-approves-mks-request-to-part-from-labor-meretz/ |title=You can go your own way: Arrangements Committee approves MK\u2019s request to part from Labor-Meretz |work=[[The Times of Israel]] |accessdate=23 March 2020 |date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n;Legend\n* '''Gov.'''\n**\u2014 Sum of the [[Thirty-fourth government of Israel|34th government]] parties: [[Likud]], [[Shas]], [[United Torah Judaism]] (UTJ), and [[Yamina (political alliance)|Yamina]].\n\n61 seats are required for a majority in the Knesset.\n\n'''Note:''' The composition of the current government does not necessarily determine the exact makeup of the post-election government.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"t